commit.message:
CESU-8: Fix encoding of codepoint U+FFFF

Fixed a problem within the CESU-8 encoder which lead to
a wrong encoded U+FFFF codepoint.

CESU-8: Fixed various decoding problems

The CESU-8 decoder wasn't suited to decode input that doesn't
indicate CESU-8 in the first byte. Now the decoder performs chunked
decoding what means it decodes everything until the first CESU-8
surrogate pair with UTF-8. Afterwards it verifies that the CESU-8
surrogate pair is within the permitted range otherwise it is probably
a 3 byte UTF-8 sequence and falls back to the UTF-8 decoder.
The CESU-8 decoder repeats this algorithm until it decoded the
full input or an error occurs.
Testing: Test with python 3.6 on travis-ci

Fixed parameters tuple access with unicode index (#98)

On executing context for a prepared statement which calls parameterized
functions, stored procedures, etc. HANA returns parametermetadata
containing the parameters name as id. On execution cursor.py used this
id for index access to the parameters tuple. Now an enumeration is used
to get the position of the current parameter/parametermetadata and for
access to the parameters tuple.

Merge pull request #73 from Multiposting/master

Truncate (instead of round) microseconds to milliseconds.

Truncate (instead of round) microseconds to milliseconds.

This ensures that the value sent to Hana for seconds and
milliseconds is in the expected range of 0-59999.
Accept PARAMETERMETADATA part while handling select response
Made py.test in Travis CI more verbose
Raise IntegrityError on unique constraint violation
